content:
Unified Messaging consolidates customer communication channels into one unified platform. You can bring your existing WhatsApp number into Unified Messaging.

Merge Marketing and Service by Migrating from WhatsApp-First Business Messaging to Unified Messaging:

* Migrate from a WhatsApp-First or externally provided WhatsApp channel to a unified WhatsApp channel
* Preserve messaging history and most channel settings
* Get access to Unified Messaging features such as Data Cloud reporting

Transfer a WhatsApp Conversation from Marketing Cloud Engagement to Service Cloud with Journey Builder:

* Transfer a WhatsApp conversation from a Marketing Cloud Engagement interaction to a Service Cloud interaction
* Pass conversation history, journey data, recipient's WhatsApp number, and cross-cloud WhatsApp phone number

View Analytics for the WhatsApp Session Transfer Activity in Journey Builder:

* Learn how customers interact with your WhatsApp journeys and why they're transferred to support
* View total, successful, and failed transfers from Marketing Cloud Engagement interactions to Service Cloud support

Suppress Promotional WhatsApp Messages During Support Interactions with Journey Builder:

* Control whether a Marketing Cloud Engagement message is sent to a customer engaged in an active or open Service Cloud support conversation

Expand the Data Available for Your WhatsApp Engagement Queries in Unified Messaging:

* Include Correlation ID, Sender Display Name, and Interactive Content Type information in your WhatsApp engagement queries
* Refine and target communications with subscribers based on query results
title: Unified Messaging Features in Salesforce
